The paper deals with the Extended Kalman Filter (EKF) and its application to navigation and Simultaneous Localization And Mapping (SLAM) problems. Therefore, the most likely category is Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of symmetries in designing EKFs, which suggests the category of Symmetry and Group Theory (cs.SY) as the second most likely category. The paper also mentions the use of computer vision techniques, which suggests the category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) as the third most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of Monte-Carlo runs and optimization-based smoothing algorithms, which suggests the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as the fourth and fifth most likely categories, respectively.
